articles.title: Bdellovibrio bacteriovorus uses chimeric fibre proteins to recognize and invade a broad range of bacterial hosts - Nature.com
articles.description: A diverse arsenal of fibre-like proteins extend outward from the B. bacteriovorus cell surface and localize towards prey cells, facilitating recognition and invasion.
